# SQLx Compile-Time Database URL
# ================================
# This database is used ONLY during compilation to verify query correctness.
# It is NOT used at runtime - applications create their own databases.
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    - Unix:    cp .env.example .env
#    - Windows: copy .env.example .env
#
# 2. Run the setup script:
#    ./scripts/setup-sqlx.sh
#
# The setup script will:
#   - Create the .tmp directory
#   - Create and migrate the database
#   - Prepare SQLx offline mode (for CI)
#   - Verify your setup
#
# Advanced: SQLx Offline Mode
# ----------------------------
# For CI or working without a database:
# 1. Run: cd libraries/soul-storage && cargo sqlx prepare
# 2. Commit the generated .sqlx/ directory
# 3. Build with: SQLX_OFFLINE=true cargo build
#
# See docs/SQLX_SETUP.md for detailed documentation
#
DATABASE_URL=sqlite:libraries/soul-storage/.tmp/dev.db
